# Code Style

## TypeScript

- Strict mode is on — never use `any`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` unless the type needs to be extended
- All exported functions must have explicit return types
- Use `const` by default; `let` only when reassignment is required
- No `console.log` in production code paths

## Svelte

- One component per file; filename must match the component name (`PascalCase.svelte`)
- All `export let` props must be explicitly typed — no implicit inference from untyped props
- Use the Svelte store in `src/lib/stores/game.ts` for shared state; do not pass deeply nested props
- Prefer `{#if}` over CSS `display: none` for toggling major UI sections
- Event handlers are named `handle<Action>` (e.g. `handleSpin`, `handleSubmit`)

## CSS

- Every color, spacing, font size, radius, and transition value must reference a CSS custom property from `src/app.css`
- No inline styles except for dynamic values that cannot be expressed as a variable (e.g. reel transform)
- No Tailwind utility classes — this project uses custom CSS only
- Mobile-first: write base styles for 375px viewport, then expand with `@media (min-width: ...)`
- Minimum touch target size for all interactive elements: 44×44px

## File Naming

- Components: `PascalCase.svelte`
- Utilities and stores: `camelCase.ts`
- Route files: SvelteKit conventions (`+page.svelte`, `+server.ts`, `+layout.svelte`)
